WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.709 --> 00:00:10.990
Sadhguru: Yoga for Inner Exploration – Shambhavi
Mudra.

00:00:10.990 --> 00:00:17.260
In the history of humanity, many truly scintillating
human beings have happened.

00:00:17.260 --> 00:00:20.849
They have shone brighter than the stars in
the sky.

00:00:20.849 --> 00:00:27.180
But why is it that one seems to have come
with enormous capability and

00:00:27.180 --> 00:00:32.259
why is it another has to struggle with every little aspect of life?

00:00:32.259 --> 00:00:38.520
If you consider yourself to be a mechanism,
you have a body and a mind.

00:00:38.520 --> 00:00:45.500
You may have a great body and a great mind
but what you call as grace is the lubrication.

00:00:45.500 --> 00:00:50.300
Without the necessary lubrication, you get
stuck at every point.

00:00:50.300 --> 00:00:56.281
Any number of people like this are there on
this planet – intelligent, capable,

00:00:56.281 --> 00:01:02.480
but at every corner in their life, they get stuck
because there is no lubrication.

00:01:02.480 --> 00:01:08.780
So it is important for a human being to have
an element of grace in their lives.

00:01:08.780 --> 00:01:13.900
Shambhavi Mudra is a process that is like
opening a window,

00:01:13.900 --> 00:01:16.900
so that one becomes receptive to grace.

00:01:20.520 --> 00:01:24.500
Here are a few guidelines that will set optimal conditions and

00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:27.380
greatly enhance your receptivity of the practices.

00:01:28.740 --> 00:01:33.520
Please ensure cell phones are either in silent mode or switched off.

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:39.440
It is advisable not to sit for the program with a full stomach or immediately after a meal.

00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:46.300
Please sit with your spine comfortably erect, hands uncrossed and palms open.

00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:51.500
These conditions will prepare you to be in a heightened state of receptivity and

00:01:51.620 --> 00:01:55.960
derive the most benefits from the practices.

00:01:56.120 --> 00:02:01.620
These practices are very safe and simple and can be done by anybody.

00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:07.840
Make sure to do everything slowly and gently and according to the instructions.

00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:14.640
If you are feeling any pain or discomfort, stop and consult a doctor.

00:02:14.640 --> 00:02:22.040
The practices we will be learning here can be done by anyone ages 7 years and above.

00:02:22.040 --> 00:02:29.160
If you wear glasses, while doing the yoga practices, please remove them and keep them aside.

00:02:29.880 --> 00:02:33.660
Sadhguru: Sit comfortably in a cross-legged posture.

00:02:33.660 --> 00:02:37.900
Keep your spine comfortably erect.

00:02:37.900 --> 00:02:42.260
We will hold yoga mudra.

00:02:42.260 --> 00:02:50.000
Make the thumb and the index finger come together
at the very tips, forming a circle between them.

00:02:50.240 --> 00:02:54.680
Let the other three fingers be straight, all
the four fingers together,

00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:58.820
without any gap between them.

00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:02.032
Holding the mudra facing upwards upon your thigh,

00:03:02.040 --> 00:03:06.060
arms and shoulders should be loose and relaxed,

00:03:06.060 --> 00:03:10.810
close your eyes and sit with
a slightly upturned face.

00:03:10.810 --> 00:03:18.810
When you sit with your face slightly upturned,
there is a natural focus between your eyebrows.

00:03:18.810 --> 00:03:21.840
Maintain this natural focus, do not concentrate,

00:03:21.840 --> 00:03:25.120
just maintain this natural focus between your eyebrows and

00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:32.420
sit with your face slightly upturned,
eyes closed.

00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:36.980
Maintain this gentle and casual focus between
the eyebrows and

00:03:36.980 --> 00:03:49.200
be conscious of the natural movement of breath.

00:03:49.210 --> 00:03:56.740
Continue to sit like this for three to six minutes.

00:03:57.680 --> 00:04:54.260
Sadhguru chants Yogarathova Bhogarathova…

00:04:54.260 --> 00:06:15.480
Instrumental Music…

00:06:15.680 --> 00:06:24.260
Sadhguru: Take your own time, take your own
time, slowly, very slowly, open your eyes.

00:06:26.360 --> 00:06:29.320
Through yoga or through pleasure, In company or alone,

00:06:29.320 --> 00:06:32.280
One who keeps his mind on Brahman (the source of creation)

00:06:32.280 --> 00:06:39.440
He enjoys, he enjoys only he enjoys.

00:06:51.720 --> 00:06:52.240
[ 5 minutes for Inner Exploration]

00:06:52.300 --> 00:06:57.720
Mysticism does not come from the East, it
comes from within.

00:06:57.720 --> 00:07:03.060
Before you attempt anything that is considered
as a mystical process,

00:07:03.060 --> 00:07:08.480
it’s very important to stabilize the five fundamental elements within us.

